@NODE req "System Requirements"

                        - System Requirements -

 Here are the system requirements for ComTracker:-


      - An Amiga compatible system                  ;-)

      - OS 2.04+

      - Asl.library

      - Amiga Installer for HD Install

      - A lot of RAM recommended

      - A kickin' stereo


 Please @{ "read on" link install} for more info

@ENDNODE

@NODE install "Installing"

                             - Installing -

 To install ComTracker (to HD I suppose), simply click on the install icon,
 and follow the prompts.

 NOTE: To install ComTracker the standard way, you need the standard Amiga
 installer.

 Please @{ "read on" link tools} for more info

@ENDNODE

@NODE tools "Tool Types"

                             - Tool Types -

 The program relies a bit on the icon tool types. To change the icon tool
 types, simply click on the icon once, and then press the right Amiga key
 and 'i'. A little information icon will come up. Simply click on the tool
 type you want to change.

 Here's what everything does:-

    DONOTWAIT - This has been put on, so if you put ComTracker on the
                WBStartup drawer, it will work without any problems.

    X - This sets the x coordinate in which the window will come up.

    Y - This is the same as above, except it's for the y coordinate.

    CX_POPUP - This one sets wether the GUI comes up as soon as you click
               on it or not. If it the option is 'YES' then the GUI will
               come up. If the option is 'NO' then it will be running as a
               commodity.

   VOLUME - This is the standard volume setting.

   CX_POPKEY - This sets the combination required to bring up the interface
               if it's hidden.

   DEFAULTPATH - This option sets where the standard path for the requester
                 is. Simply change this to wherever you keep your music
                 modules.

   PATTERN - This sets the pattern the requester displays. For example, if
             the pattern is set to '#?.med' it will look for modules names
             that have a .med extension.


                             - Defaults -

 If it can't find the .info file, here's what the defaults are:-

           X=0
           Y=11
           CX_POPUP=YES
           VOLUME=64
           CX_POPKEY=Ctrl Alt t
           DEFAULTPATH=
           PATTERN=#?

 Please @{ "read on" link usage} for more info.

@ENDNODE

@NODE usage "Using ComTracker"

                               - Usage -


 First of all, as you might imagine, you have to click on the ComTracker
 icon, to load the program.

 If you have the @{ "tool type" link tools} 'CX_POPUP=NO' then you should
 press the combination for the interface to come up. The default setting
 'Ctrl Alt t'. You can also bring up the interface by loading the Exchange
 manager, and clicking on 'Show Interface'.

 Once the interface (GUI) is up, you will be faced with a series of of
 GadTools gadgets. Here's what each of them do:-


    Song - This GTText simply displays the name of the current module
           loaded.

    Type - This GTText tells you whether it's a MED or MOD.

    Time - Displays how much time it has been going since you started the
           music module.

 History - This GTListView shows all the modules you have loaded so far. To
           load any of them again, simply click on their name.

    Play - This GTButton simply plays the module.

    Stop - Stops/Pauses the current module.

   Cont. - If the module has been stopped, it will continue.

    Load - Brings up an Asl Requester, in which you select the desired
           module.

    Hide - This button hides the interface, and makes the program run in
           the background. Press the CX_POPKEY combination to bring the
           interface back up.

    Quit - This one quits the progam completely.

  Slider - With this slider, you can change the volume at which the modules
           play.

    Help - This GTText displays an On-Line help, which as you move your
           pointer around the window, tells you about each gadget.


 A simple procedure:-


 1. Load the program.

 2. Click on the 'Load' gadget.

 3. Select the module you want, and click on 'OK'

 4. Click on 'Play'.

 5. Click on the close gadget to make it run in the background.


 Please @{ "read on" link history} for more info

@ENDNODE

