@NODE bugs "Known Bugs"

                               - Known Bugs -


 Here are some of the known bugs, which if I get enough feedback, I will
 fix in the near future:-


 - If you haven't got much memory, the help and time displays will flicker,
   quite badly on some machines. I've got an A1200 with a Blizzard 1230
   Mk4 with 2Mb Chip mem and 4Mb Fast mem, and it runs alright. However, I
   tried it without the Blizzard, which left me with 2Mb Chip mem, and it
   DID flicker.

 - It sometimes doesn't recognise a type of MED module. I think it's
   because of the new types of saving on programs like OctaMED or something
   like that.

 - It doesn't quit properly sometimes, and then it has a recoverable error.

 Please @{ "read on" link author} for more info
@ENDNODE

